  <data name="billingperiod.title" xml:space="preserve"><value>Billing Cycle Settings</value></data>
  <data name="billingperiod.breadcrumb.energy" xml:space="preserve"><value>Energy Management</value></data>
  <data name="billingperiod.hint.overview" xml:space="preserve"><value>Set the utility-bill start/end dates for each billing period (month); periods without custom settings default to starting the day after the previous period ends, lasting one month (calendar month if nothing is customized). Changes take effect immediately — all monthly reports (Energy Report / Refrigeration Ton Report / EMS pages) are split by billing period, and historical monthly reports are recalculated with the new settings.</value></data>
  <data name="billingperiod.hint.gap_overlap" xml:space="preserve"><value>Gaps or overlaps between periods are allowed (warning only): energy in a gap is not counted in any period, and energy in an overlap is counted in both periods.</value></data>
